{"id": "software-development--python-companion-radio-room-server-and-repeater-supporting-lora-and-esp-now", "title": "Python companion radio, room server and repeater, supporting LoRa and ESP-NOW", "forum": "software-development", "messages": [{"id": "1432881415514755102", "author": "BW", "author_handle": "brianwiddas", "user_id": "1242432422063374357", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Tuesday, October 28, 2025 7:59 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-10-28 7:59 p.m.", "text": "https://github.com/brianwiddas/meshcore-pi Python implementation of a companion radio, room server and repeater for Raspberry Pi (or other Linux box) ● Run multiple profiles at once (eg. companion radio and room server) ● Repeaters and room servers can use keys for authentication rather than passwords ● Room server welcome messages ● SX126x interfaces on Raspberry Pi ● ESP-NOW if the WiFi interface has monitor mode ● Can use any existing companion radio (eg a Heltec) as a LoRa or ESP-NOW interface", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve><a href=\"https://github.com/brianwiddas/meshcore-pi\">https://github.com/brianwiddas/meshcore-pi</a>\n\nPython implementation of a companion radio, room server and repeater for Raspberry Pi (or other Linux box)\n\n● Run multiple profiles at once (eg. companion radio and room server)\n● Repeaters and room servers can use keys for authentication rather than passwords\n● Room server welcome messages\n\n● SX126x interfaces on Raspberry Pi\n● ESP-NOW if the WiFi interface has monitor mode\n● Can use any existing companion radio (eg a Heltec) as a LoRa or ESP-NOW interface</span></div>", "embeds_html": ["<div class=chatlog__embed><div class=chatlog__embed-color-pill style=background-color:rgba(30,35,39,255)></div><div class=chatlog__embed-content-container><div class=chatlog__embed-content><div class=chatlog__embed-text><div class=chatlog__embed-title><a class=chatlog__embed-title-link href=https://github.c